/div></div></div></section><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the Patient Mobile App in the Virtual Practice?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Patient Mobile App is the native iOS and Android application that comes with your Virtual Practice. It lets patients securely log in, book appointments, view health records, pay bills, and communicate with providers — all from their smartphones."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the Patient Mobile App free for clinics to use?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Every Virtual Practice includes access to the free ContinuousCare patient app, which patients can download from the iOS App Store or Google Play. Clinics don't need to pay extra for their patients to use it."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I have the app under my own brand name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Startups and clinics that want their own branded app can choose the white-label option. This paid add-on publishes the app under your organization's App Store and Play Store accounts, with your name, logo, and branding."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What can patients do with the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients can:\n\nBook video or in-person appointments\n\nView prescriptions, test results, and medical history\n\nReceive smart notifications and reminders\n\nPay bills online\n\nManage family member accounts\n\nSync health data automatically from supported devices"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the app integrate with Apple Health and Google Health Connect?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients can grant permission to sync data from Apple Health (iOS) or Google Health Connect (Android) directly into their Virtual Practice health record. White-label apps also support additional Bluetooth health device integrations."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the Patient Mobile App secure?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The app follows the same security and compliance standards as the Virtual Practice web portal. Data is encrypted in transit and at rest, and only patients and their authorized providers can view health information."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can providers send information to patients through the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Providers can share prescriptions, lab results, consultation notes, and care plan updates directly in the app. Patients receive instant notifications when new information is available."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do patients still have access to the web portal if they use the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The web portal and the mobile app are fully synchronized. Patients can use either or both, depending on their preference."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who supports patients if they face issues with the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The app is only a secure interface to each provider's Virtual Practice. Patients should contact their clinic or healthcare provider for help related to appointments, services, or care."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can clinics turn off the mobile app and only use the web portal?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Clinics that prefer not to use the mobile app can direct patients to use the web portal only. The choice is fully up to each Virtual Practice."}}]}</script><section class="py-16 bg-gray-50"><div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"><div class="text-center mb-12"><h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="w-24 h-1 bg-blue-vibrant mx-auto"></div></div><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8"><div class="border-b border-gray-200 last:border-b-0"><button aria-label="What is the Patient Mobile App in the Virtual Practice?" class="w-full text-left py-4 flex justify-between items-center h